INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (74, 'Siem Reap –Rolouse Group& Kampong Phluk with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap –Rolouse Group& Kampong Phluk with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will explore the earliest Angkor capital in the region Hariharalaya near the contemporary town of Rolous. In Rolous Group you will visit Preak Ko, Bakong, and Lolei temple. Then continue to the road ahead and use a variety of transportation to reach Kompong Phluk. Kompong Phluk, meet some fishermen and families and you also can see floating houses, floating forest, floating school….\r\n\r\n  Note: The boat fee is $25 per person (Alone) and $20/person from 2people up.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 40.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:17:09');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (75, 'Siem Reap –Rolouse Group& Kampong Khleang with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap –Rolouse Group& Kampong Khleang with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will explore the earliest Angkor capital in the region Hariharalaya near the contemporary town of Rolous. In Rolous Group you will visit Preak Ko, Bakong, and Lolei temple. Then continue to Kompong Khleang, which is located on the northern edge of Tonle Sap Lake about 50km from the city center. At Kompong Khleang you will visit floating houses, floating school, and floating forest.\r\n\r\n  Note: The boat fee is $25 per person (Alone) and $20/person from 2people up.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 60.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:17:42');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (76, 'Siem Reap–Golden Silk farm&West Baray with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–Golden Silk farm&West Baray with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nFirst you will visit the Golden Silk Farm produces unique, individual silk pieces from the yellow silkworm, traditionally found in Southeast Asia and it located about 18km from the Siem Reap city. Then you continue to West Baray. The west Baray is one of the largest hand cut water reservoirs on Earth, possessing a current maximum capacity of 12 to 14 billion gallons of water (53 million m3) and you can have lunch with local food at there and you also can relax on the hammock in the local small lodge. \r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 40.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:18:22');
