INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (78, 'Siem Reap–City Tour with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–City Tour with Car Only	Departure : 08:00 AM\r\n\r\nFirst you will visit Killing field at Wat Thmei of Thmei pogoda, then you continue to Angkor National museum, next you will visit praying place called Preah Ang Chek and Preah Ang Chorm, and Royal Residence. After that you continue to Preah Promrath pagod to find out about Baddis, next you can explore the local market called Old market or Phsar Chas and the last you visit Artisan DÁngkor which is craft place.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 25.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:27:37');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (79, 'Siem Reap–City Tour + countryside+sunset with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–City Tour + countryside+sunset with Car Only	Departure : 13:00PM\r\n\r\nFirst you will visit Killing field at Wat Thmei of Thmei pogoda, then you continue to Angkor National museum, next you will visit praying place called Preah Ang Chek and Preah Ang Chorm, and Royal Residence. After that you continue to Preah Promrath pagod to find out about Baddis, next you can explore the local market called Old market or Phsar Chas to test local foods, and visit Artisan DÁngkor which is craft place. The last you will visit lotus farm and Phnom Krom to visit sunset on the top of the hill.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 40.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:29:23');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (80, 'Siem Reap–National Park (Phnom Kulen) with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–National Park (Phnom Kulen) with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will visit Phnom Kulen, translating to \'Lychee Mountain\' is the most sacred mountain in Cambodia and it takes about 2hrs reach this mountain. On the top of this mountain you will visit Preah Ang Thom which is a sacred to the Khmer and it is pilgrimage site for Buddhists and Hindus. After you will continue to 1000 Linga and Yonis were carved into the riverbed, which a King had diverted over them to make the water sacred and fertile. Then you will go to the river tumbles down two waterfalls, at the base of the larger one is a refreshing swimming area.\r\n\r\n	Note: The entrance fee is $20/person.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 70.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:30:00');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (81, 'Siem Reap–National Park (Phnom Kulen) + Beng Melea with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–National Park (Phnom Kulen) + Beng Melea with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will visit Phnom Kulen, translating to \'Lychee Mountain\' is the most sacred mountain in Cambodia and it takes about 2hrs reach this mountain. On the top of this mountain you will visit Preah Ang Thom which is a sacred to the Khmer and it is pilgrimage site for Buddhists and Hindus. After you will continue to 1000 Lingas and Yonis were carved into the riverbed, which a King had diverted over them to make the water sacred and fertile. Then you will go to the river tumbles down two waterfalls, at the base of the larger one is a refreshing swimming area. Then continue to Beng Melea temple which is ancient temple. \r\n\r\n	Note: Phnom Kulen fee is $20/person, Beng Melea fee is $5/person.\r\n\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 80.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:31:01');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (82, 'Siem Reap–Koh Ker Temple with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–Koh Ker Temple with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will visit Koh Ker is one of the more remote, seldom visited temple complexes in the area, over 100km northeast of Angkor built between 928 and 944 under King Jayavarman IV, and his son, Harshavarman II.  This complex has many unique temples, although dominated by Prasat Thom, with striking similarities to the Mayan temples.\r\n\r\n	Note: Koh Ker fee is $10/person\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 95.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:31:38');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (83, 'Siem Reap– Koh Ker+ Beng Melea with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap– Koh Ker+ Beng Melea with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will visit Koh Ker is one of the more remote, seldom visited temple complexes in the area, over 100km northeast of Angkor built between 928 and 944 under King Jayavarman IV, and his son, Harshavarman II.  This complex has many unique temples, although dominated by Prasat Thom, with striking similarities to the Mayan temples.\r\nThen continue to Beng Melea temple which is ancient temple. \r\n\r\n	Note: Koh Ker fee is $10/person, Beng Melea fee is $5/person.\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 100.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:32:11');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (84, 'Siem Reap– Koh Ker+ Preah Vihear with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap– Koh Ker+ Preah Vihear with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will visit Koh Ker is one of the more remote, seldom visited temple complexes in the area, over 100km northeast of Angkor built between 928 and 944 under King Jayavarman IV, and his son, Harshavarman II.  This complex has many unique temples, although dominated by Prasat Thom, with striking similarities to the Mayan temples. Then continue to Preah Vihear Temple to explore on foot to the temple, wonderfully preserved.  After you will continue your discovery to the top, you clinging to the cliffs of the Dang Rek Mountain, which rises a few hundred meters above the Cambodian plains. \r\n\r\n	Note: Koh Ker fee is $10/person, Preah Vihear Temple fee is $5/person and Climbing car (4 x4) $25/car\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 160.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:32:49');
INSERT INTO `item` VALUES (85, 'Siem Reap–Preah Vihear with Car Only', '1DAY 	Siem Reap–Preah Vihear with Car Only	Departure : 08:00AM\r\n\r\nToday you will explore on foot to the temple of Preah Vihear Temple, wonderfully preserved. Some tourists spend the Thai border to visit each day, but most will have left the scene for a long time and you will have the privilege to walk the fabulous complex only. After you will continue your discovery to the top, you are clinging to the cliffs of the Dang Rek Mountain, which rises a few hundred meters above the Cambodian plains. The different views from most breathtaking mountain temples are a beauty to take your breath away.\r\n\r\n	Note: KPreah Vihear Temple fee is $5/person and Climbing car (4 x4) $25/car\r\n', 'INCLUSIONS\r\n\r\n•	Air-conditioned vehicle ( 4 seats)\r\n•	Mineral water\r\n', 135.00, NULL, 7, 4, 1, NULL, NULL, 19, '2019-08-29 16:33:32');
